    <string name="privacy_policy_title">Privacy Policy</string>
    <string name="privacy_policy_content">
        <b>Last Updated: March 9, 2026</b>\n\n
        Your privacy is our top priority. VaultPass is an <b>offline-first</b> password manager, which means:\n\n
        <b>1. Local Storage Only</b>\n
        All your passwords, notes, and sensitive data are stored exclusively on your device. We do not have servers and cannot access your data.\n\n
        <b>2. Encryption</b>\n
        Your vault is protected using industry-standard encryption. Access is only possible with your Master Password.\n\n
        <b>3. No Data Collection</b>\n
        VaultPass does not track your usage, collect personal information, or share any data with third parties.\n\n
        <b>4. Your Responsibility</b>\n
        Since we do not store your Master Password, it is impossible for us to recover it if lost. Please keep it safe.
    </string>
